VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is just not doable for most people. So, if you want to save yourself some time and money and try out Hero for yourself. I\'ll leave a link to it in the top of the description. And if you use the code YouTube, you\'ll get a 10% discount on'

[06:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your first 3 months. Now that we have all of our motion graphics ready, we can move on to the next step, creating a voice over. When creating voiceovers, I like to use a texttospech tool like 11 Labs, which in my opinion has the most'

[07:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'realistic voices and it\'s really easy to use. All you got to do is paste in your script into this text box. Pick a good voice, hit generate, and you\'ll have your voice over ready in a few seconds. It\'s not always perfect right away,'

[07:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'though, so you might have to regenerate it a couple of times to get a good result. Then all you got to do is click on this button to download it to your computer. So, now that we have the motion graphics and the voice over ready, the final thing we need to do is'

[07:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to put it all together with some sound design in an editing software. Since all the animations is already done in Hera, you\'re not going to need to do any crazy editing. Personally, I use Adobe Premiere Pro, but you\'ll be able to follow along in whatever editing'

[07:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'software that works for you. So, let\'s start off by importing the voice over and drag it down to the timeline. The thing with AI voices is that they usually have these weirdly long pauses. So, what I like to do is to add the J'

[07:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cuts. It\'s when you remove these silent moments and slightly overlap sound bars. This will give the voice over a better flow and make it sound more realistic. Now you just want to continue repeating the same process until you\'ve added J'

[08:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cuts throughout the entire voice over. Next, you want to import all of the motion graphics you created in Hera. Now start adding the motion graphics to the timeline and place them above their matching part of the voice over. Once'

[08:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you\'ve added all of the motion graphics to the timeline, there\'s really not much editing that needs to be done to the visuals, but there\'s still a lot of work that needs to be done to the sound design. The first thing we need to do is add some music. Vox usually uses some'

[08:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'kind of minimal instrumental beat and the best way I found to find similar copyright free music is to use a website like Pixabay. So I just headed over there, searched for documentary music and found one I thought would fit the'

[08:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video. Downloaded it from Pixabay, dragged it down to the timeline and adjusted the volume so that it\'s not too loud. Finally, we need to add some sound effects to make the animations feel more alive. For example, when a text or a'

[09:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'graph is popping up in the animations. Now, let\'s take a look and see how the final video turned out. &gt;&gt; For decades, we\'ve been told that the world\'s population is exploding, that one day there\'ll be too many people for the planet to handle. Governments are'

[09:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'now warning of a different crisis. Not overpopulation, but underpopulation. In 1900, there were about 1.6 billion people on Earth. By the year 2000, that number had quadrupled to more than 6'

[09:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'billion. And today, we\'re at about 8 billion. But here\'s the plot. The rate of growth now actually is slowing down. The reason comes down to fertility rates. Globally, that number has dropped from about five in 1960 to just 2.3 today. And in many countries like Japan,'

[09:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'South Korea, Italy, even China, it\'s already below replacement level, which is about 2.1. Without spending hours in an editing software, we managed to create a professional looking voxy documentary only using Hera. So, if you'

[09:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
